/-- Suppose f is holomorphic on a neighborhood of the closed unit disk and f(0) â‰  0. Then
there exists C such that for all m and |z| â‰¤ 1,
|1 - Î£_{k=0}^m f^{(k)}(0)/(k! f(0)) z^k| â‰¤ C |z|^{m+1}.
-/
theorem jirilebl_ca_ca_12552 {f : â„‚ â†’ â„‚}
  (hf : âˆ€ z, |z| â‰¤ 1 â†’ AnalyticAt â„‚ f z) (h0 : f 0 â‰  0) :
  âˆƒ C : â„, âˆ€ m : â„•, âˆ€ z : â„‚, |z| â‰¤ 1 â†’
    |1 - (Finset.range (m+1)).sum fun k => ((iteratedDeriv k f 0) / ((Nat.factorial k : â„‚) * f 0)) * z ^ k|
      â‰¤ C * |z|^(m+1) := by sorry
